 {"title": "Salesforce-native routing and lead-to-account matching", "detail": "Chili Piper reads Salesforce in real time during the booking flow. Lead-to-account matching, territory-based routing, and account owner prioritization all happen before the prospect sees a calendar. Routing rules can reference any standard or custom Salesforce field. This depth of CRM integration is something Calendly can't match."},
 {"title": "Advanced distribution logic for complex sales orgs", "detail": "Round-robin with weighting, territory-based assignment, segment-based routing, and capacity limits give sales ops teams fine-grained control over lead distribution. You can route enterprise leads to senior reps, SMB leads to a different pool, and existing accounts to their owner. All of this happens automatically during the booking flow."},
 {"title": "Handoff product preserves deal momentum", "detail": "The Handoff product lets SDRs instantly schedule meetings for AEs during a qualifying call. The SDR sees the AE's real-time availability, books the meeting, and the prospect gets a calendar invite before the qualifying call ends. No 'let me check their calendar and get back to you.' The warm handoff happens while the prospect is engaged."},
