 {"title": "Enterprise Sales Team with Territory-Based Routing", "description": "A 60-person enterprise sales team organized by territory and segment uses Chili Piper Distro to route inbound leads. When a VP of Engineering at a Fortune 500 company fills out a contact form, Chili Piper checks Salesforce for an existing account and owner. If found, the lead routes to the account owner. If new, Distro routes based on territory (geography), segment (company size), and rep capacity. The rules took 2 weeks to configure but eliminated the manual lead routing process that previously took 30 minutes per lead and resulted in 4-hour average response times."},
 {"title": "SDR Team Doing Warm Handoffs to AEs", "description": "A 25-person SDR team uses Chili Piper Handoff to schedule meetings for AEs during qualifying calls. When an SDR confirms a lead is qualified, they pull up the assigned AE's availability in Chili Piper, propose times to the prospect on the spot, and book the meeting before the call ends. The prospect gets a calendar invite with the AE's name and a Zoom link within seconds. Before Handoff, SDRs would end the call, email the AE, wait for availability, then email the prospect. Average time from qualification to booked meeting dropped from 26 hours to 3 minutes. Show rates improved from 62% to 81%."},
